SrI bodhAyanamaharShi praNItAni mahAnyAsa sUtrANi
========================

Here bodhAyanamaharShi is giving the mahanyaasa in a capsule form. 
He is directly teaching the mahanyaasa method (vidhiM vyAKyAsyAmaH). 

oM athAtaH pa~jcAMgarudrANAM nyAsapUrvakaM japahomArcanABiShekavidhiM vyAKyAsyAmaH ||
( pa~jcAMgarudrasya ayamartthaH pa~jcaprakArAH aMganyAsAH yeShu te pa~jcAMga rudrAH | evaM ShaDaMgarudrasyApi ShaTprakArAH aMganyAsAH yasya saH ityartthaH | tatra SiKAdyastraparyantaM ekatriMSadaMganyAsaH digbandha sahitaH prathamaH)

nyAsam 1 - (SiKAdyastraparyantaM ekatriMSadaMganyAsaH digbandha sahitaH prathamaH)
=======
1. yAte rudreti SiKAyAM | asmin mahatyarNNava iti Sirasi |
sahasrANIti lalATe | ha(gm)saH SuciShaditi Bruvormaddhye |
tryaMbakaM yajAmahe iti netrayoH |  namaH srutyAyeti karNNayoH |
mAnastoka iti nAsikAyAM | avatatyeti muKe | nIlagrIvau dvau kaNThe | 
namaste astvAyudhAyeti bAhvoH | yA te hetirityupabAhvoH |  
pariNo rudrasya hetiriti maNibandhayoH |  ye tIrtthAnIti hastayoH | 
sadyojAtamiti pa~jcAnuvAkAn pa~jcasvaMgulIShu |   
namo vaH kirikeBya iti hRudaye |  namo gaNeBya iti pRuShThe |   
namo hiraNyabAhava iti pArSvayoH | vijyaM dhanuriti jaThare |   
hiraNyagarBa iti nABau | mIDhUShTameti kaTyAM |   
ye BUtAnAmadhipataya iti guhye | ye anneShvityaNDayoH |
saSirA jAtavedA ityapAne | mAno mahAntamityurvoH | 
eShate rudra BAga iti jAnvoH | sa(gm)sRuShTajiditi jaMGayoH |
viSvaM BUtamiti gulphayoH | ye pathAmiti pAdayoH | 
addhyavochaditi kavacaM | namo bilmina ityupakavacaM |
namo astu nIlagrIvAyeti tRutIyaM netraM | 
pramu~jca dhanvana ityastraM | ya etAvantaSceti digbandhaH ||

nyAsam 2 - (mUrddhAdipAdAntaM daSAM~gganyAsaH dvitIyaH)
=======

2. oM namo Bagavate rudrAyeti namaskArAn nyaset | 

i) oM~gkAraM mUrddhni vinyasya nakAraM nAsikAgrataH | 
mokAraM tU lalATe vai BakAraM muKamaddhyataH || 

ii) gakAraM kaNDadeSe tu vakAraM hRudi vinyaset | 
    tekAraM dakShiNe haste rukAraM vAmato nyaset || 

iii) drAkAraM nABideSe tu yakAraM pAdayor nyaset || 

nyAsam 3 - pAdAdimUrddhAntaM pa~jcAMganyAsaH tRutIyaH
=========
3   i) sadyaM ca pAdayornyasya vAmaM nyasyorumaddhyataH |
	aGoraM hRudi vinyasya muKe tat puruShaM nyaset || 

     ii) ISAnaM mUrddhani vinyasya haMso nAmasadASivaH |
	 haMsa haMseti yo brUyAt haMso nAma sadASivaH | 

     iii) evaM nyAsavidhiM kRutvA tataH saMpuTamAraBet | 

     iv)  trAtAramindraM, tvaMno agne, sugaM naH panthAM, asunvantaM, tatvA yAmi, Ano niyudBiH | 
           vaya(gm)soma, tamISAnaM, asme rudrA, syonApRuthivItyetat saMpuTaM indrAdi dikShU vinyasya
           evamevAtmani ShoDaSaraudrIkaraNaM kRutvA viBUrasItyanuvAkena sAnuSha~ggeNa || 

      v)  tvagasthigataiH sarvapApaiH pramucyate sarvaBUteShvaparAjito Bavati |  
           tato BUtapreta piSAca brahmarAkShasa yakSha yamadUta SAkinI DAkinI sarpa SvApada vRuScika taskarAdyUpadravAdyUpaGAtAH ||

      vi) sarve (grahAH) jvalantaM paSyantu |   mAM rakShantu | 

nyAsam 4 - guhyAdimastakAnta ShaDaMganyAsaH caturtthaH
4   	manojyotiH, aboddhyagniH, agnirmUrddhA, mUrddhAnaM, marmANi te, jAtavedA, 
iti guhya-nABi-hRudaya-kaNTha-muKa-SirAMsyaBimantrya AtmarakShA karttavyA brahmAtmanvadasRujatetyanuvAkena | 
 
nyAsam 5 - hRudayAdya strAntaM ShaDaMganyAsaH pa~jcamaH
=======
5) 	Sivasa~gkalpaM hRudayaM, puruShasUktaM SiraH, uttaranArAyaNaM SiKA, apratirathaM kavacaM, pratipuruShadvayaM
	netraM, SatarudriyamityastraM | 

       korvai for Sivasa~gkalpaM
       1.  yenedaM, yena karmANi, yenakarmANyapaso, yat praj~jAnagM, suShArathir, yasminnRuco, yadatra ShaShThaM, yajjAgrato, yenedaM, yena dyauH pRuthivI daSa |

	2.  ye mano hRudaya, macintya, mekA ca, ye pa~jca, vedAhametaM, yasyedaM dhIrAH, parAt parataraM caiva, 
parAt parataro brahmA, yA vedAdiShu, yo vai devaM daSa |

	3.  prayato, yo&sau, goBir juShTaM, kailAsa SiKare, tryaMbakaM, viSvataScakShu, Scaturo vedAn, 
mAno mahAnta, mmAnastoka, Ruta(gm) satyaM daSa |

	4.  kad rudrAya, brahmajaj~jAnaM, yaH prANato, ya AtmadA, yo rudro, gandhadvArAM, ya ida(gm) Sivasa~gkalpa(gm) saptatri(gm)Sat.

pa~jcAMgaM sakRutjapet - ha(gm)saH SuciShat,  pratadviShNuH, tryaMbakaM, tatsaviturvRuNImahe, viShNur yonimiti | 

	aShTAMgaM praNamya - hiraNyagarBo, yaH prANato, 	brahmajaj~jAnaM, mahIdauH, upaSvAsaya, agne naya,
yAte agne, imaM yama ityaShTA~ggaM praNamya | 

	athAtmAnaM SivAtmAnaM SrIrudrarUpaM dhyAyet | 
	(*athAtmAnaM rudrarUpaM dhyAyet pa~jcamuKaM SivaM |  iti pAThAntaraM| ) 

	i)	SuddhasphaTikasa~gkASaM trinetraM pa~jcavaktrakaM
		gaM~ggAdharaM daSaBujaM sarvABaraNa BUShitaM |

	ii) 	nIlagrIvaM SaSA~gkA~gkaM nAgayaj~jopavItinaM
		vyAGracarmmottarIyaM ca vareNyamaBayapradaM | 

	iii) 	kamaNDalvakShasUtre ca dadhAnaM SUlapANinaM
		jvalantaM pi~ggaLajaTaM SiKAmaddhyodadhAriNaM

	iv)	amRutenAplutaM hRuShTaM divyaBogasamanvitaM
		digdevatA samAyuktaM surAsuranamaskRutaM| 

	v) 	nityaM ca SASvataM SuddhaM dhruvamakSharamavyayaM
		sarvavyApinamISAnaM rudraM vai viSvarUpiNaM |
		evaM dhyAtvA dvijaH samRuk tato yajanamAraBet | 

	athAto rudrasnAnArcanABiShekavidhiM vyAKyAsyAmaH ||

	Adita eva tIrtthe snAtvA, udetya ahataM vAsaH paridhAya,
	SuciH prayato brahmacArI SuklavAsAH, ISAnasya pratikRutiM
	kRutvA tasya dakShiNApratyagdeSe tanmuKaH sthitvA, Atmani
	devatAH sthApayet | 

nyAsam 6 - ayaM ShaShThaH nyAsaH

6) prajanane brahmA tiShThatu | pAdayoH viShNustiShThatu |  
hastayoH harastiShThatu | bAhvorindrastiShThatu |   
jaThare agnistiShThatu | hRudaye SivastiShThatu |   
kaNThe vasavastiShThantu | vaktre saraswatI tiShThatu |
nAsikayorvAyu stiShThatu | nayanayoScandrAdityau stiShThatAM | 
karNNayoraSvinau stiShThatAM |  lalATe rudrAstiShThantu |
mUrddhanyAdityAstiShThantu | Sirasi mahAdevastiShThatu |
SiKAyAM vAmadevastiShThatu | pRuShThe pinAkI stiShThatu | 
purataH SUlI stiShThatu | pArSvayoH SivASa~gkarau stiShThatAM |
sarvato vAyu stiShThatu | tato bahIH sarvato&gnir jvAlAmAlAparivRutastiShThatu | 
sarveShva~ggeShu sarvAdevatA yathAsthAnaM tiShThantu |  mAM (sakuTuMbaM) rakShantu | 

agnirmme vAci Srita iti yathAliMgaM aMgAni saMspRuSya AtmAnaM gandhapuShpadhUpadIpa naivedyaiH mAnasaiH  ArAdhayet | 

athainaM prasAdayet | 

ArAdhito manuShyaistvaM siddhair devAsurAdiBiH |
ArAdhayAmi BaktyA tvA&nugrahANa (tvAM mAM gRuhANa) maheSvara | 

AtvA vahantu harayaH sacetasaH SvetairaSvaiH sahaketumadBiH | 
vAtAjitair balavadBiH manojavairAyAhi SIGraM mama havyAya SarvoM |   
tryaMbakamiti ca, ityAvAhayati, sthApite tu na AvAhanaM| 

atha AsanaM | dadAti sadyo jAtamiti | Bave Bava iti pAdyaM | 
BavodBAvAya namaH ityarghyaM | vAmadevAya namaH ityAcamanIyaM | 
athainaM snapayati |   
Apo hiShThAdiBiH tisRuBiH, hiraNya varNNA iti, pavamAnaH suvarjanaH ityanuvAkena mArjayitvA, 
sarvo vai rudraH, kayA naScitraH, apo vA id(gm) sarvaM ityetaiSca, 
vAmadevAya namaH iti vastraM, jyeShThAya namaH ityupavItaM, rudrAya namaH ityAcamanIyaM,
praNavena BUShaNaM, kAlAya namaH iti gandhaM, kalavikaraNAya namaH ityakShatAn, 
balavikaraNAya namaH iti puShpaM, balAya namaH itidhUpaM,
balapramathanAya namaH iti dIpaM, sarvaBUtadamanAya namaH iti naivedyaM,
manonmanAya namaH iti tAMbUlaM dadAti | 

athAsmai aShTaBirmmantraiH aShTau puShpANi dadAti 'BavAya devAyanamaH' ityAdi |   
athAsya aghoratanUrUpatiShThate aGoreByo&thaGoreByaH iti,
atha rudragAyatrIM japet, tat puruShAya vidmaha iti SatakRutvaH
aparimita kRutvaH vA daSavAraM vA |  
athainaM ASiShamASAste,  ISAnaH sarva vidyAnAM iti | 

athasya mUrddhani hiraNyakalaSena santatadhArAM niShi~jcet | 
madhunA sarpiShA payasA cekShurasena Amrarasena vA nALikerodakena
vA tadalABe udakena vA namaste rudramanyava ityekAdaSAnuvAkAn japet | 
japAnte agnAviShNu sajoShasetyekAdaSAnuvAkAn  pratyekamekamekaM japet | 
sarveShAM pAre punarArAdhayet uttamArAdhanena | 

tena aBiShiktodakena akShIByAM ityanuvAkena abli~ggAdiBiScha A pAdAt saMspRuSya pApakShayArtthI vyAdhivimokShArtthI SrIkAmaH SAntikAmaH puShTikAmaH tuShTikAmaH AyuShkAmaH ArogyakAmaH
evaM kuryAt |  evaM kUrvan siddhimavApnoti | 

AcAryAya dakShiNAM dadAti | daSa gAH savatsAH suvarNNaBUShitAH vRuShaBaikAdaSAH tadalABe ekAM gAM dadyAt |   ekAdaSa brAhmaNAn Bojayet | aSvamedhakratusahasraphalamavApnotItyAha BagavAn bodhAyanaH| 

|| iti bodhAyana maharShi praNItAni mahAnYAsasUtrANi || 

SuBaM

